To dream..<br>
<br>
He tried not to.  Dreams were terrible things.  Horrid nightmares of wicked visions that clawed and clenched in his guts and tore him screaming from his sleeping pallet, drenched in cold sweat with his heart pounding so loud he feared others might wake and hear it.  He would sit there, shivering, trembling, trying desperately not to weep though he wanted too so very badly; to cry out his fear and beg for their protection from the demons that waited for him, just beyond the veil of sleep.<br>
<br>
It never showed.  <br>
<br>
When he was out and about his daily duties, there was no sign of his terror.  While he ate meals with his companions there were no slips in his speech to betray his soul-leeching weariness.  If his bretheren saw a look on his face during a battle that they did not recognize, they said nothing of it, or simply dismissed it as the tensions of the moment.<br>
<br>
But it was always there, waiting, whispering to him.  It knew he must come back.  It knew it would have him in it's horrid clutches again very soon, and it told him so.  It reminded him of his coming fate and that there was no hiding from it, no running from it, no escape.....no hope......nevermore.  <br>
<br>
He would lie awake at night, making the sleeping noises that others expected.  He fought the fatigue, the cry for rest that his body demanded.  He even heard others, thinking they were the only ones awake, rise and creep out on their own business, to return some time later and re-assume their former places confident that they alone knew.  <br>
<br>
In the end, it was futile.  The darkness would take him, suddenly, and without warning.  The veil between worlds would part, and they would decend upon him again, as he lay there bare and defenseless for another night.  <br>
<br>
The torments were unspeakable.  The pain was real, as real as waking, but it burned so much more...  It drove him to the brink of madness.  Held him there on the razor's edge of sanity as he gibbered and moaned and wept like a beaten child.  They mocked him there.  Skittering, chittering, scrabbling things teased and stung and poisoned him as dark faded wraiths of wisp and shadow sank their talons into his soul; his soulsblood to run in dim streams around their claws as they cackled and whispered and screamed as only the dying can scream.  <br>
<br>
He felt tearing deep inside.  Bone cracking, sinews popping, muscle ripping free from it's normal station.  His screams grated the air as his tormentors screeched their laughter at his weakness and pain.  They were going to finish him this time.  They were going to tear him to pieces.  Gods please let them finish.  Let them end it now Please!<br>
<br>
Cold air seared his lungs as he lurched up from his sleeping pallet, the scream frozen on his lips as the pain faded from his flesh, from his soul.  He sat there for the remainder of the night, quivering, cold, alone.  <br>
<br>
He musn't tell.<br>
<br>
He must be strong.<br>
<br>
<br>
In the silence, he heard dark laughter, echoing away......<br>
<br>
